{
  "stem": "12491.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as I mentioned before, after Schindler's, Schindler's speech on May 7-- I think it materialized exactly that way.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He has left the camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On May 8, in the morning, the camp gates were opened.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Germans were gone, and we, we, we, the 28-- I think it's 28-- people have taken over the guarding of the camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We-- the camp itself was located on the site of a rather main highway.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were approximately 100 kilometers east of the American front and about 100 kilometers west of the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were actually in no-man's land.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We found out from people who were free, who knew what things are going, going on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I, I didn't know how I knew that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now I know it, because probably somebody told me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is why it took several days before anyone from the-- either side would have come to our camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The person who came actually was a Russian soldier on a horse, and very haggard.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And told us, you are now free.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I think he spent, spent few minutes, like an hour maybe, and left.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He told us that eventually, administration will come and they will take care of the camp, of the people of the camp.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Prepare us for repatriation and back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Since we were on the, on the side of the main road, and since the Germans have capitulated-- and they did not want to fall into the Russian hands, they preferred to fall into American hands-- they started, on the-- in large groups, walking from the east to west towards the American lines, to fall in American POW camps.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They had to pass in front of our camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
